[normal]Written [bold]submission from the[bold] London Councils and the [bold]London Procurement Strategy Board[bold] (LPG 31)[bold]The following is a response on behalf of London Councils and the London Procurement Strategy Board
[normal]London Councils is a cross-party organisation, representing London’s 32 boroughs
[normal] and the 
[normal]City of London.  
[normal]The London Procurement Strategy Board (LPSB) is the principal, strategic procurement board for London local government.  It brings together senior finance and procurement officers to develop and deliver a procurement strategy for London local government.  
